  "prompt": "What percentage of commission do sellers need to pay e-commerce websites like Flipkart, eBay, Amazon, Shopclues, Shimply, Myntra etc., when selling clothing such as t-shirts?",
  "response": "The commission, often called \"referral fees\" or \"marketplace fees,\" charged by e-commerce websites like Flipkart, Amazon, Myntra, etc., for selling clothing like t-shirts varies depending on several factors:\n\n*   **Specific Website:** Each platform has its own commission structure.\n*   **Product Category:** Clothing has its own category-specific fee structure.\n*   **Selling Price:** Commissions can be tiered based on the selling price of the item.\n*   **Seller Tier/Agreement:** Larger sellers or those with negotiated agreements might have different rates.\n*   **Other Fees:** In addition to the referral fee, there can be other fees like shipping fees (if the platform handles shipping), closing fees, payment processing fees, and advertising costs (if the seller chooses to advertise).\n*   **Promotional Offers:** Platforms may offer temporary discounts on commissions as part of promotional programs.\n\n**General Commission Ranges for Clothing (as of late 2023 and early 2024, but subject to change):**\n\nKeep in mind that these are ESTIMATES and can change, so checking each platform's official documentation is critical.\n\n*   **Amazon India:** Referral fees for clothing (including t-shirts) can range from **around 5% to 15%**.\n*   **Flipkart:** Commission rates are competitive and are around **5%-12%** depending on product type.\n*   **Myntra:** Myntra often has a higher commission structure due to its focus on fashion brands. Commission charges from **6% to 15%**\n*   **EBay:** Fees depend on product category, starting as low as **3%**\n*   **Others:** Shopclues and other smaller platforms would be in the similar range of **5-15%.**\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Check the Platform's Official Documentation:** The most accurate and up-to-date information is always on the specific e-commerce platform's seller help pages or fee schedules. Look for sections like \"Selling Fees,\" \"Referral Fees,\" or \"Commission Rates.\"\n*   **Factor in Other Costs:** Don't forget to factor in shipping costs, packaging, payment processing fees, and any advertising expenses when calculating your profitability.\n*   **Negotiation (for Larger Sellers):** If you are a high-volume seller, you might have the ability to negotiate custom commission rates with the platform.\n*   **GST (Goods and Services Tax):** Keep in mind that GST may be applicable on the commission fees charged by the e-commerce platforms.\n\n**How to Find the Specific Commission Rate for Your T-shirts:**\n\n1.  **Go to the Seller Central/Seller Panel of the platform you are interested in.**\n2.  **Search for \"Selling Fees\" or \"Referral Fees\" or \"Commission Rates.\"**\n3.  **Look for the clothing category (or a more specific subcategory like \"T-shirts\").**\n4.  **The table or document should list the percentage charged based on the selling price.**\n\n**Example Scenario:**\n\nLet's say you are selling a t-shirt for \u20b9500 on Amazon India. The referral fee for clothing is 8%. You would pay Amazon a commission of \u20b940 (8% of \u20b9500). You may also have other fees like shipping if Amazon handles the shipping.\n\n**In Summary:**  There is no single answer to the percentage commission. You MUST research each platform individually to get the accurate, current rate for your specific product.\n",
